==Dutch==

===Etymology===
From {{etyl|odt|nl}} *{{term||hervist|lang=odt}}, from {{proto|Germanic|harbistaz|lang=nl}}. Related to High German {{term|Herbst|lang=de}}, English {{term|harvest|lang=en}}, Latin {{term|carpere||to [[pick]], to [[pluck]]|lang=la}}, Greek {{term|καρπός|tr=karpos||fruit, harvest|lang=grc}}. The original meaning is ''harvest time'', as is seen in {{term|herfstmaand|lang=nl}}.

===Pronunciation===
* {{IPA|/ɦɛr(ə)fst/|lang=nl}}, {{X-SAMPA|/h\Erfst/|lang=nl}}
* {{audio|nl-herfst.ogg|Audio (Netherlands)}}

===Noun===
{{nl-noun|m|-|-}}

# [[autumn]], [[fall]]

====Usage notes====
The made-up compound noun {{term||herfstschrik|fear of Autumn}} ({{IPA|/hɛrfstsxrɪk/|lang=nl}}, {{X-SAMPA|/hErfstsxrIk/}}) is used to demonstrate the bewildering number of consonants that can be strung together in Dutch. It is not particularly difficult for a speaker of Dutch to pronounce all consonants, but in practice a few of these will be dropped to something like {{IPA|/hɛrfsxrɪk/|lang=nl}}, {{X-SAMPA|/hErfsxrIk/}}.

